  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6978.76 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (14.8B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level while providing support on dips toward 6975 and the flip at 6894. The PIN regime with strong positive gamma concentration creates a powerful magnet effect around current levels, with dealers mechanically dampening volatility through contrarian hedging flows. Key resistance at 7000 should cap upside momentum, while the wall_break detection suggests we've likely breached a significant support level below, potentially triggering additional dealer buying to stabilize price.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong resistance at 7000 with choppy, range-bound action between 6950-7000.",
